    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>JAPANESE BOND DOWNGRADE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tanikawa, Miki</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Moody's downgrades Japanese government bonds to Aa2 from Aa1 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Moody's has downgraded yen-denominated Japanese government bonds to Aa2 from Aa1. The agency cited the fact that Japan has the highest ratio of debt as a percentage of gross domestic product among the leading economies and uncertainty over Japan's economic recovery. There was a brief sell-off of stocks and bonds after the rating announcement and then a recovery.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa (NYT)</p>
      </block>
